This paper is primarily focused on weight initialization in neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, the paper also discusses the theoretical insights into weight initialization with non-linear activations, which could also be relevant to other sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
